did.head: Overview
did.unittitle: Stanford University, Sponsored Projects Office, records
did.abstract: Records from the Sponsored Projects Office include correspondence, memoranda, reports, minutes, patent files, and financial records.

repository.label: Repository:
repository.corpname: Department of Special Collections and University Archives

accessrestrict.head: Information about Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research; materials must be requested at least 24 hours in advance of intended use.

userestrict.head: Ownership & Copyright
userestrict.p: Property rights reside with the repository. Literary rights reside with the creators of the documents or their heirs. To obtain permission to publish or reproduce, please contact the Public Services Librarian of the Dept. of Special Collections.

prefercite.head: Cite As
prefercite.p: Stanford University Sponsored Projects Office Records, SC 344. Stanford University Archives, Stanford, Calif.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content of Collection
scopecontent.p: Records from the Sponsored Projects Office pertain to administrative matters and to individual projects; included are correspondence, memoranda, reports, minutes, patent files, and financial records. Many of the correspondence files are those of Earl Cilley. Specific topics include the Solar Energy Research Institute, 1976-77; the BALLOTS project, 1975; the NIRT project; the Te Vega research ship; the Stanford Electronics Laboratory; the San Joaquin Basin Analysis Project; indirect cost recovery; the Committee on Research; and the Committee on Government Relations.
Accession 1983-158 includes records related to the Solar Energy Research Institute, 1976-77, and the BALLOTS project 1975.
